<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>PMS - About Us</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="~/img/title_logo.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/AboutUsStyle.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>
        <img src="~/img/PMS_logo.png" alt="PMS logo" class="main-logo">
    </h1>

    <div class="container-wrapper">
        <div class="about-container">
            <h2>About PMS</h2>

            <div class="about-section">
                <h3><span class="icon">&#128736;</span> What is PMS?</h3>
                <p>
                    The <strong>Piping Management System (PMS)</strong> is a comprehensive web-based platform
                    purpose-built for managing piping fabrication and erection activities in industrial
                    construction projects. It provides end-to-end visibility and control over every stage of
                    the piping lifecycle — from engineering drawings and joint records through welding,
                    inspection, testing, and final release.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section">
                <h3><span class="icon">&#127919;</span> Our Mission</h3>
                <p>
                    To streamline construction project workflows by replacing manual tracking with a
                    centralized, real-time digital system. PMS empowers project teams — engineers, QC
                    inspectors, welding coordinators, and management — to collaborate efficiently, reduce
                    errors, and accelerate project delivery while maintaining full traceability and
                    compliance.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section">
                <h3><span class="icon">&#128640;</span> Key Modules</h3>
                <div class="modules-grid">
                    <div class="module-card">
                        <h4>&#128202; Dashboard</h4>
                        <p>Real-time project overview with spool status summaries, progress charts, and key metrics at a glance.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="module-card">
                        <h4>&#128295; Welders Qualifications</h4>
                        <p>Manage welder registrations, qualification records, and WRR status tracking across projects.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="module-card">
                        <h4>&#128221; Logs</h4>
                        <p>Transmittal logs and status, RFI tracking, WPS (Welding Procedure Specification) management, and Painting logs.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="module-card">
                        <h4>&#128196; Daily Input</h4>
                        <p>Daily Fit-up Reports (DFR), Daily Welding Reports (DWR), RT/HT selection, and productivity planning.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="module-card">
                        <h4>&#128200; Status Tracking</h4>
                        <p>Spool fabrication and erection status, joint progress monitoring, NDE and hydrotest tracking.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="module-card">
                        <h4>&#128209; Engineering</h4>
                        <p>Drawings management, joint record analysis, NDT percentage calculations, and hydrotest flagging.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="module-card">
                        <h4>&#128274; Administration</h4>
                        <p>User login approval, project configuration, control lookups, and role-based access management.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="module-card">
                        <h4>&#128231; Communication</h4>
                        <p>Built-in contact forms, automated email notifications for daily fit-up reports, and team collaboration tools.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="module-card">
                        <h4>&#128462; Reports</h4>
                        <p>Professional PDF reports with grouped layouts, banded detail rows, and project branding — DFR, DWR, Welder List, and more.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section">
                <h3><span class="icon">&#128187;</span> Technology</h3>
                <div class="tech-badges">
                    <span class="tech-badge">ASP.NET Core 8</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">C#</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">Entity Framework Core</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">SQL Server</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">Razor Views</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">JavaScript</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">Chart.js</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">Azure AI Services</span>
                    <span class="tech-badge">QuestPDF</span>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="about-section">
                <h3><span class="icon">&#9989;</span> Why PMS?</h3>
                <p>
                    PMS replaces fragmented spreadsheets and manual paperwork with a unified, auditable
                    digital platform. With role-based access control, real-time dashboards, automated
                    reporting, and full traceability from material receipt to final testing, PMS ensures that
                    construction projects stay on track, on budget, and fully compliant with industry
                    standards.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="back-link-container">
                @{
                    var referer = Context.Request.Headers["Referer"].ToString();
                    var isFromDashboard = !string.IsNullOrEmpty(Context.Session.GetString("FullName"));
                }
                @if (isFromDashboard)
                {
                    <a href="@Url.Action("Dashboard", "Home")" class="back-link">Back to Dashboard</a>
                }
                else
                {
                    <a href="@Url.Action("Login", "Home")" class="back-link">Back to Login</a>
                }
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer">
        <div class="footer-left"></div>
        <div class="footer-center">
            This system is strictly restricted to authorized users only.<br>
            &copy; 2025 Piping Management System. All rights reserved.
        </div>
        <div class="footer-right">
            <img src="~/img/work-smarter-not-harder.jpg?v=3" alt="Logo" class="footer-logo" />
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
